  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to demonstrate and quantify the micro architecture and micro
      vascular changes within skeletal muscles after marathon using 3T MRI (diffusion tensor and
      arterial spin labeling). Apparent diffusion coefficient, fractional anisotropy and flow
      parameters will be registered before and after the long-distance run on the lower leg. Axial
      T1 and axial SPAIR sequences will also be applied at the same time.Stress ox and inflammatory
      markers will be collected in blood and urine samples and compare with both MRI and
      Near-infrared spectroscopy (NIRS).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
